<TITLE> PM lobbied for land reforms </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 22 (bdnews24.com)Civil society leaders have pressed the prime minister for a land commission for reformation of the country's farmlands and wetlands. Sheikh Hasina told the economists, who met her Sunday, the government would look into the matter and place it for discussion in parliament. Economists Rehman Sobhan, Anisur Rahman, MM Akash, Abul Barakat, NGO leaders Shamsul Huda and Khusi Kabir called on the prime minister at her official Hare Road residence. Abul Barakat told reporters afterwards, "Awami League pledged in their election manifesto to redistribute Khas lands, including wetlands, to poor farmers and fishermen." "Development of the people is not possible without reformation, including redistribution, of farmlands and wetlands," Barakat said. AL also mentioned forming a land reform commission in their manifesto, he said. bdne
